    <h2>Signs Your Melbourne Flue Needs Cleaning Now</h2>
    <p>Don't wait until there's a problem. If any of these apply, your flue needs attention before the next fire:</p>
    <div class="signs-grid">
      <div class="sign-card">
        <span class="sign-icon">&#128293;</span>
        <div class="sign-title">Smoke coming back into the room</div>
        <div class="sign-desc">The most common sign of a restricted flue. Creosote buildup narrows the flue and prevents proper draw — smoke has nowhere to go except back in.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="sign-card">
        <span class="sign-icon">&#128168;</span>
        <div class="sign-title">Smoky smell when the fire isn't lit</div>
        <div class="sign-desc">Creosote off-gases in warm weather and when air flows down the flue. A persistent smoke smell with no fire going almost always means an uncleaned flue.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="sign-card">
        <span class="sign-icon">&#9888;&#65039;</span>
        <div class="sign-title">Fire struggles to draw or stay alight</div>
        <div class="sign-desc">A heavily sooted flue restricts airflow. Fires that are hard to light, won't stay alight, or produce too much smoke are usually flue restriction problems.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="sign-card">
        <span class="sign-icon">&#9889;</span>
        <div class="sign-title">Visible black tar or soot around the collar</div>
        <div class="sign-desc">If you can see black residue weeping from the flue collar or around the firebox, creosote has built up to a significant level and needs removal.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="sign-card">
        <span class="sign-icon">&#128038;</span>
        <div class="sign-title">Bird noises or scratching from the flue</div>
        <div class="sign-desc">Melbourne's starlings and sparrows nest in unused flues over summer. A nest blocks the flue entirely — don't light a fire until it's been cleared.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="sign-card">
        <span class="sign-icon">&#128197;</span>
        <div class="sign-title">It's been more than 12 months</div>
