    <h2>How Often Should a Flue Be Cleaned in Melbourne?</h2>
    <p><strong>Once a year is the standard recommendation</strong> — and it's the right schedule for most Melbourne homes in regular winter use. Melbourne's heating season typically runs May through August, with fireplaces and wood heaters used heavily for 4–5 months of the year.</p>
    <p>The ideal time to book is <strong>March or April</strong> — before the season starts, before every other Melburnian has the same idea, and while your flue has a full summer's worth of any bird activity or moisture ingress to deal with before winter.</p>
    <div style="background:var(--bw);border-left:4px solid var(--ba);border-radius:0 var(--rad) var(--rad) 0;padding:1.2rem 1.25rem;margin-top:1rem;">
      <p style="margin:0;font-size:1.03rem;line-height:1.65;color:var(--ts);"><strong style="color:var(--tm);">When to clean more frequently:</strong> If you burn every day through winter, use unseasoned wood, or your flue runs on an outside wall (colder flue = more condensation = faster creosote buildup), twice a year is worth considering. Holiday homes that sit unused over summer are also higher risk for bird nests — check before lighting the first fire of the season.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

